    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "```js\r\nconst staticRefinementList = instantsearch.connectors.connectRefinementList(\r\n  ({ items, refine, widgetParams }, isFirtRender) => {\r\n    const container = document.getElementById('brand-list');\r\n    if (isFirtRender) {\r\n      container.addEventListener('click', event => {\r\n        const input = event.target.closest('input');\r\n        if (input) {\r\n          refine(input.value);\r\n        }\r\n      });\r\n      return;\r\n    }\r\n    const list = widgetParams.values.map(staticItem => {\r\n      const { isRefined } = items.find(\r\n        item => item.label === staticItem.label\r\n      ) || {\r\n        isRefined: false,\r\n      };\r\n      return `\r\n        <li>\r\n          <label>\r\n            <input\r\n              type=\"checkbox\"\r\n              value=\"${staticItem.value}\"\r\n              ${isRefined ? 'checked' : ''}\r\n            />\r\n            ${staticItem.label}\r\n          </label>\r\n        </li>\r\n      `;\r\n    });\r\n    container.innerHTML = `\r\n      <ul>\r\n        ${list.join('')}\r\n      </ul>\r\n    `;\r\n  }\r\n);\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n  staticRefinementList({\r\n    attributeName: 'brand',\r\n    values: [\r\n      { label: 'Apple', value: 'Apple' },\r\n      { label: 'Microsoft', value: 'Microsoft' },\r\n    ],\r\n  })\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\nSomething like this, but with menu instead of refinement list should do the job you want, I think ",
